<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Rain and storms stretched Wednesday from Pennsylvania into North  
Carolina, with dry skies and fair conditions in the nation's 
midsection. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy rain and storms struck Virginia and the mid-Atlantic  
region, along with Alabama and western Georgia. 
</P>
<P>
	High pressure continued to bring fair and dry weather from the  
central and southern Plains into the Mississippi Valley. 
Temperatures remained hot across Oklahoma and Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	A trough of low pressure moved into the Dakotas and Nebraska,  
bringing showers to western North Dakota south into the Nebraska 
panhandle. Utah and Colorado also received rain. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair and dry weather prevailed along the West Coast.  
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the lower 48 states was 100 degrees in  
Blythe, Calif. The low was 28 degrees in Sanford, Maine. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
