<HEADLINE> New Houston Stadium Behind Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- The Astros' new home is behind schedule.  
</P>
<P>
	The retractable-roof stadium in downtown Houston is scheduled to  
be ready for opening day next spring, but the general contractor 
said it is 24 days behind schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown &AMP; Root's project manager, Steve Smith, still is promising  
the park will open April 1 as scheduled. The first regular season 
game is April 7 against the Philadelphia Phillies. The facility, 
which replaces the Astrodome, is 75 percent complete. 
</P>
<P>
	Members of the Harris County-Houston Sports Authority also were  
told Tuesday that Brown &AMP; Root has been submitting claims that 
could push the cost past the budget limit. 
</P>
<P>
	But the authority's construction committee chairman said he  
still believes the price will come in under $250 million. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
