<HEADLINE> London Share Prices Rise / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Share prices rose Wednesday on the London Stock  
Exchange, led by telecommunication and bank shares, on hopes that 
the second interest rate rise in eight weeks by the U.S. Federal 
Reserve will be the last for the year. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 index closed up 54.4  
points, or 0.9 percent, at 6,369.5, on provisional volume of about 
1 billion shares. 
  	   	
</P>
