<DOCNO> APW19990825.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-25 18:10:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nebraska's QB Hopeful Fields Punts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Nebraska quarterback Bobby Newcombe,  
hampered last season by a knee injury, is so sure he's healthy 
he'll go as far as returning punts to prove it. 
</P>
<P>
	Newcombe, battling Eric Crouch for the Cornhuskers' quarterback  
job, fielded three punts during a two-hour workout Wednesday. He 
said it wouldn't be a surprise if he returns kick during the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	``That's a lot of fun,'' Newcombe said after the practice, not  
worried about being leveled by a special-teams players who has 40 
yards to build up steam. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's always a risk involved. But there's a bigger risk  
playing quarterback than punt returner. Standing back in the pocket 
or throwing the ball on an option play, you get hit every play,'' 
Newcombe said. ``But standing back on a punt return, you're either 
giving a shot or running with the ball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Newcombe wouldn't be the first quarterback to do double-duty as  
a punt returner. John Hadl, a former NFL great in the 1960s, 
routinely returned kicks when he played at Kansas. But it is 
unusual for a quarterback to pull such double duty. 
</P>
<P>
	Newcombe returned punts two years ago when the Cornhuskers, who  
had Scott Frost starting at quarterback, were desperate to get the 
speedy freshman into the game. His 244 yards on 12 punt returns 
(20.3 yards per return) led the team. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, Newcombe replaced Frost at quarterback, but tore a  
knee ligament and played only six games. 
</P>
<P>
	Nebraska coach Frank Solich said he won't rule out letting  
Newcombe return punts again, but he's stopping short of naming the 
6-foot junior as his top returner. 
</P>
<P>
	``I wouldn't get too excited about anything at this point on  
that end of it,'' Solich said. ``There's a lot of things to 
consider before we go forward with that kind of decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd consider it,'' Solich said. ``If he did return maybe two  
or so punts I don't think you're putting him at that much risk.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
