<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Down in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0444 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0518 Tuesday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the 
euro traded at $1.0436. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Tuesday,  
included 110.90 Japanese yen, down from 111.48; 1.5320 Swiss 
francs, up from 1.5212; 1.4944 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4962. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5890, down from $1.5971.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 111.11 yen and  
the pound was worth $1.5856. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8727 German marks, up from 1.8595; 
6.2807 French francs, up from 6.2365; 2.1100 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0952; 1,853.95 Italian lire, up from 1,840.91. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold in London was quoted at $252.70 bid per troy ounce, down  
from $253.40 on Tuesday. In Zurich the bid price was $252.45, down 
from $253.25. Gold fell $0.90 in Hong Kong to close at $253.45. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver in London was quoted at $5.06 bid per troy ounce, down  
from $5.14. 
  	   	
</P>
