<HEADLINE> Disney Sorry for Radio Promotion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Walt Disney Co. has apologized for a  
promotion at one of its radio stations that distributed plastic 
gardening tools called ``Black Hoes'' as gag prizes to listeners 
and advertisers. 
</P>
<P>
	Disney issued the apology Tuesday after black groups in Los  
Angeles called for a boycott against the entertainment giant. 
</P>
<P>
	``The promotion could be viewed as offensive and derogatory,''  
Steven Bornstein, president of Disney's ABC division, said in a 
statement. ``We sincerely apologize to our employees and anyone 
else for any offense that has been taken.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The promotion was run last year by Disney's KLOS-FM radio  
station and aired nationwide on its syndicated ``Mark &AMP; Brian'' 
show. A black employee at the station sued her employers, saying 
she was harassed by managers and co-workers after she complained 
about the promotion. 
</P>
<P>
	In the lawsuit, she complained that ``ho'' is a derogatory term  
for prostitute. 
</P>
<P>
	The Congress of Racial Equality said it would press on with a  
national boycott of Disney despite the apology. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is much too little and too late,'' said Sandra Moore, the  
group's vice chairwoman. 



  	   	
</P>
