<HEADLINE> U.S. Commends Russian Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The United States commended Russian  
peacekeeping forces Wednesday for their attempts to enter a town in 
Kosovo blockaded by ethnic Albanians. 
</P>
<P>
	``We believe that they are taking a very measured and  
professional approach to the problem and are determined to resolve 
the situation by negotiation,'' said State Department deputy 
spokesman James B. Foley. 
</P>
<P>
	But in the deeply divided town of Orahovac, appeals from the  
United States and others failed to persuade ethnic Albanians to 
abandon their makeshift roadblocks and allow Russian peacekeepers 
to enter the town. 
</P>
<P>
	``The standoff continues,'' Foley said.  
</P>
<P>
	But, he said, ``we are confident that at the end of the day the  
Russian troops will be able to fulfill their mandate and that they 
will perform professionally and even-handedly, as they have 
elsewhere.'' 
  	   	
</P>
