<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Revolution 2, MetroStars 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Jeff Baicher, John Harkes and  
Giovanni Savarese scored shootout goals Wednesday to lift the New 
England Revolution to a 2-1 victory over New York-New Jersey, 
extending the MetroStars' losing streak to a Major League 
Soccer-record 10 games. 
</P>
<P>
	The Revolution snapped a seven-game losing streak.  
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars' goal came in the 14th minute when Sasa Curcic  
followed a run down the sideline with a pass to Mike Duhaney, who 
put the ball into the upper right corner of the goal. 
</P>
<P>
	Three minutes later, Duhaney was carried off the field after  
tearing a knee ligament in a tangle with Baicher. 
</P>
<P>
	New England tied it in the 46th minute on Joe-Max Moore's low  
shot into the right corner, his 12th goal of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars missed an opportunity in the 57th minute when  
Curcic's free kick was backheaded off the post by Nansha Kalongi 
and Billy Walsh's rebound was saved by New England goalkeeper Jeff 
Causey. 
</P>
<P>
	John Harkes' goal in the 89th minute was waved off due to an  
offside call. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
