<HEADLINE> Browns Get Jamie Martin as 2nd QB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEREA, Ohio (AP) -- Cleveland Browns coach Chris Palmer has found  
a backup quarterback who won't take long to learn his offensive 
scheme. 
</P>
<P>
	Jamie Martin was the reserve quarterback last season for the  
Jacksonville Jaguars, filling in for starter Mark Brunell in a 
victory against Detroit last December. In Martin's only NFL start, 
the next week against Tennessee, he tore a knee ligament, ending 
his season. 
</P>
