Terms weren't disclosed, but his agent, Jack Mills, had said 
earlier that the Browns were offering a one-year minimum contract 
of $400,000. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's close to being ready,'' Palmer said. ``His familiarity is  
a factor.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Palmer said Martin could provide the Browns a reserve with  
experience. The starter is expected to be veteran Ty Detmer, with 
rookies Tim Couch and Mike Cook the backups. With the addition of 
Martin, Cook would probably be added to the practice squad. 
  	   	
