<HEADLINE> Your Halo Wins Feature at Del Mar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Your Halo overtook favored Mr. Fortune in  
the final furlong to win Wednesday's $58,000 feature race at Del 
Mar by 1 1/4 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Garrett Gomez and carrying high weight of 123 pounds,  
Your Halo covered six furlongs in 1:09 1-5 and, as the 3-1 second 
choice in the field of seven, paid $8.60, $4 and $3 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the fifth in 12 lifetime starts for Your Halo  
and was worth $34,800, increasing the career earnings of the 
4-year-old son of Jolie's Halo to $158,510. 
</P>
<P>
	Mr. Fortune, the 19-10 favorite ridden by Kent Desormeaux and  
carrying 119 pounds, crossed the finish line 4 1/2 lengths ahead of 
Hilltown and returned $3.60 and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Hilltown, a 28-1 longshot ridden by Isaias Enriquez and carrying  
119 pounds, was a neck in front of Nor' Easter at the wire and paid 
$5.40 to show. 
  	   	
