<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Krivokrasov Agrees To Counseling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Nashville Predators all-star forward  
Sergei Krivokrasov must undergo counseling as part of an agreement 
for dismissal of a domestic violence charge brought by his wife. 
</P>
<P>
	The charge stemmed from disagreement Aug. 8 at the couple's home  
in New Buffalo, Mich. In a police report, Natalia Krivokrasov said 
that following an argument her husband kicked and slapped her, 
pulled out a handful of her hair and pushed her down three steps. 
</P>
<P>
	Krivokrasov, 25, pleaded innocent and was scheduled for trial  
Thursday at Berrien County Trial Court in Michigan. He faced a 
93-day jail sentence if convicted. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement was reached Tuesday at a pretrial hearing, Berrien  
County prosecutor James Cherry said. The case will be reviewed in 
six months. 
</P>
<P>
	``If he gets counseling, has no further incidents and everything  
seems to be on the up and up ... then the matter will be 
dismissed,'' Cherry said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Krivokrasov's agent, Mike Gillis, said his client will submit to  
counseling. 
</P>
<P>
	``He and his wife regret the events of that evening and are  
actively working at reconciling their differences,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Predators general manager David Poile said that in compliance  
with NHL policy, Krivokrasov will meet with league officials to 
assess his counseling needs. 
</P>
<P>
	Poile said the team does not plan any disciplinary action  
against Krivokrasov, the Predators' leading goal-scorer last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``We obviously don't condone the activity, but we do support the  
Krivokrasovs and we do hope and pray that their problems can be 
worked out,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Krivokrasov had 25 goals and 23 assists during Nashville's  
inaugural season. His 48 points were third-best on the squad and 
earned him a one-year contract worth $850,000, which he signed last 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-foot-10, 185-pound Krivokrasov led the team with six  
game-winning goals and 10 power-play goals, and was the only 
Predator selected for the NHL All-Star game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
