<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise in Early Trading / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar slipped against the yen early Thursday,  
while Japanese stocks rose moderately following another record 
close on Wall Street. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 111.18 yen, down 0.14 yen from late Wednesday  
in Tokyo but higher than its late New York level of 111.14 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 46.08  
points, or 0.26 percent, to 17,901.24 in the first 30 minutes of 
trading. On Wednesday, the average closed down 240.25 points, or 
1.33 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar was slightly higher from its  
New York level after a rally in U.S. Treasury bonds and the robust 
showing Wednesday on Wall Street attracted investor interest in the 
greenback. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders said the dollar may remain in a tight range the rest of  
Thursday trading as enthusiasm among overseas investments funds for 
Japanese stocks will continue, thus curbing the dollar's rise. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 115.90 yen, down  
from 116.84 yen late Wednesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, prices rose after posting steep falls in  
the past two sessions. 
</P>
<P>
	High-tech issues were leading the market in early morning  
trading following strong gains by technology issues on the New York 
Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York on Wednesday, the Dow Jones industrial average  
finished at a record high 11,326.04 points, up 42.74, or 0.4 
percent. U.S. stocks shot up as investors expressed confidence that 
the American economy can continue to grow without runaway 
inflation. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 1.74 points, or 0.12 percent, to 1,496.54. The 
TOPIX closed down 12.27 points, or 0.81 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose  
to 2.0400 percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.9950 percent, 
driving its price down to 98.83 yen from 99.20 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
