<HEADLINE> Husband Kills Wife, Then Himself </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A man shot and killed his wife as their children  
slept, called his mother to tell her, then went to a boathouse and 
shot himself, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Harry Haynes, 39, shot his wife Debra Haynes, 44, numerous times  
Tuesday night at the couple's Queens Village home. He then phoned 
his mother in Brooklyn. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told her he had killed his wife and asked her to take care  
of the kids,'' said a police source, speaking on condition of 
anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	Haynes then drove to his mother's home, threw his house keys on  
her front steps and drove away, the source said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police spotted Haynes' unoccupied car parked near a park  
Wednesday morning. Soon after they heard a gunshot and found Haynes 
dead with a single gunshot wound to his head. 
</P>
<P>
	The children, an 8-year-old girl and 5-year-old boy, were taken  
to a hospital for evaluation. 
</P>
<P>
	Haynes had been a letter carrier for 11 years when he retired in  
1997 for personal reasons, U.S. Postal Service spokesman Tom Gaynor 
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
