<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Domingo Dropped From Tax Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BERLIN (AP) -- Placido Domingo has been dropped from a German tax  
evasion probe after agreeing to pay an undisclosed sum. 
</P>
<P>
	Hubert Jobski, a prosecutor in the city of Mannheim, would not  
reveal the amount Wednesday or say whether it went to state coffers 
or charity. 
</P>
<P>
	Luciano Pavarotti and Jose Carreras, who toured with Domingo as  
the Three Tenors, remain under investigation, Jobski said. 
</P>
<P>
	All three opera stars were named as suspects in November in an  
investigation of German concert promoter Matthias Hoffmann. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffmann was charged with funneling huge sums of money for the  
stars and himself to shell companies outside Germany. He was 
convicted in December of evading taxes on $8 million and was 
sentenced to nearly six years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors dropped a related case against soprano Montserrat  
Caballe last month after she agreed to pay more than $53,000. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
