<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	Cameron Diaz, born on Aug. 30, 1972, is one of the stars of  
``Being John Malkovich,'' directed by Spike Jonze. The film is 
being shown out of competition at this year's Venice Film Festival, 
which opens Sept. 1. 

</P>
<P>
	Salma Hayek drew a crowd in Veracruz, Mexico, at the July 8  
premiere of ``Nobody Writes to the Colonel,'' a movie based on a 
short novel by Nobel laureate Gabriel Garcia Marquez. Hayek, born 
on Sept. 2, 1968, is set to star in the life story of Mexican 
artist Frida Kahlo, which will be produced by Hayek's own company. 

</P>
<P>
	Comedian Damon Wayans tackles the cult of personality in his  
book, ``Bootleg,'' published this summer by HarperCollins. Wayans, 
born on Sept. 4, 1960, received two Emmy nominations as a writer of 
``In Living Color,'' a sketch comedy show on the Fox network. When 
asked why he decided to write the book, Wayans quipped: ``I wanted 
to see if I could spell.'' He quickly added: ``Nah, I just wanted a 
challenge.'' 

</P>
