<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jackson Wins 110 Hurdles Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEVILLE, Spain (AP) -- Colin Jackson of Britain regained the  
world championships title in the 110 meter hurdles today, beating 
Anier Garcia of Cuba in a tight race. American Duane Ross was 
third. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson, who set the world record of 12.91 in the final of the  
1993 championships, had enough with a time of 13.06 seconds to take 
the gold this time. Garcia set a Cuban record in 13.07. Ross ran a 
personal best of 13.12 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first gold medal for Britain in the championships.  
</P>
<P>
	American Mark Crear, the top performer this year, was  
disqualified for two false starts in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Defending champion and Olympic gold medalist Allen Johnson of  
the United States withdrew before the semifinals with a right calf 
injury, depleting the event of its two top stars. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
