<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fidelity, CBS Sign Ad Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Fidelity Investments and CBS Corp. have signed an  
advertising agreement worth a reported $50 million that includes a 
sole sponsorship for a weekly feature on CBS' evening news 
broadcast. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal will put Fidelity advertisements in almost every market  
in the country and includes specially designed slots on drive-time 
radio, cable television, local affiliates, national news and 
Internet sites. 
</P>
<P>
	As part of the agreement, Boston-based Fidelity will sponsor a  
segment on the ``CBS Evening News with Dan Rather'' called ``The 
American Dream.'' The segment will debut Sept. 15, run every 
Wednesday, and will be an upbeat feature on people who pursue and 
achieve their dreams. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither CBS nor Fidelity would discuss the value of the deal,  
but the trade magazine Advertising Age Tuesday reported the $50 
million figure. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
