<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Glasgow Advances to European Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Glasgow Rangers advanced to the 32-team European Champions Cup  
despite a 1-0 loss to Parma on Wednesday night in the second leg of 
the third and final qualifying round. 
</P>
<P>
	Glasgow, which won the opener of the home-and-home, total-goals  
series 2-0 two weeks ago at Parma, advanced on 2-1 aggregate. 
Parma, which got a 68th-minute goal from Johan Walem, failed to 
join AC Milan, Lazio of Rome and Fiorentina in the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Fiorentina won 2-0 at Poland's Widzew Lodz on goals by Enrico  
Chiesa and Sandro Cois to advance on 5-1 aggregate. 
</P>
<P>
	Chelsea advanced with a scoreless tie against Skonto Riga in  
Latvia, advancing on 3-0 aggregate. It joined Manchester United and 
Arsenal in the final 32. 
</P>
<P>
	Dynamo Kiev, a semifinalist last year, tied Denmark's Aalborg  
2-2 at home on Maksim Shatskikh's goal in the final minute and 
advanced on 4-3 aggregate. 
</P>
<P>
	Heiko Herrlich's header with two minutes left gave Borussia  
Dortmund a 1-0 victory at home to FK Teplice. Borussia Dortmund, 
which won the tournament in 1996, advanced on 2-0 aggregate. 
</P>
<P>
	Teams will be drawn into eight four-team groups on Thursday at  
Monte Carlo, Monaco. The top two teams in each group advance to the 
second round. 
</P>
<P>
	Losers in the final qualifying round go into the draw for the  
UEFA Cup. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
