<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Gives Birth Secretly and Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OREM, Utah (AP) -- A woman awaiting trial in the unattended birth  
and death of her baby gave birth alone again in her apartment and 
died along with the infant. 
</P>
<P>
	Darcie Jo Baum, 26, apparently bled to death after giving birth.  
Her body was found Tuesday in a hall outside the bathroom. The body 
of her newborn son was in the toilet. 
</P>
<P>
	Preliminary autopsy results Wednesday showed the newborn was  
full term and born alive, Orem Police Lt. Ned Jackson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Baum had been awaiting trial on a charge of desecration of a  
body -- the most serious charge prosecutors could bring because it 
was unclear whether the other newborn was stillborn or if Ms. Baum 
had left it to die. 
</P>
<P>
	That body was found in August 1998 wrapped in a red handmade  
quilt in a grove of trees. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Baum had denied killing the baby or allowing it to die. Her  
lawyer, Randy Spencer, said he did not know she was pregnant again. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies were discovered after Ms. Baum's mother called her  
daughter's apartment Tuesday morning, Jackson said. Ms. Baum's 
4-year-old son answered and said his mother couldn't come to the 
phone. When she called back, the boy said his mother was lying on 
the floor. 
</P>
<P>
	Police officers found the boy standing near his mother's body,  
Jackson said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
