<HEADLINE> Yankees' Prospect Throws No Hitter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- New York Yankees' minor league pitcher David  
Martinez threw a seven-inning no-hitter in the first game of a Gulf 
Coast League doubleheader Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez retired the first 10 hitters he faced in the Yankees'  
5-0 win over the Tigers before issuing the first of three walks. 
The left-hander had six strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was just locked in with everything he was throwing,''  
manager Ken Dominguez said. ``David really has been our most 
consistent starter all year long and it doesn't surprise me to see 
him have that kind of command and throw a no hitter.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez, 19, was signed as a free agent in 1996 and is from  
Ciudad, Venezuela. 
  	   	
