<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-25 18:20:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Actor Martin Lawrence Collapses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	THOUSAND OAKS, Calif. (AP) -- Actor Martin Lawrence collapsed  
while jogging in 100-degree weather and lay in a coma for three 
days before regaining consciousness, hospital officials said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawrence was running in heavy clothing to try to lose weight for  
a movie role, putting himself near death when his body temperature 
rose to more than 107 degrees, hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawrence, 34, who starred in TV's ``Martin'' and the movies  
``Life,'' ``Bad Boys'' and ``Nothing to Lose,'' was listed in 
critical but stable condition Wednesday at Los Robles Regional 
Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
	The actor was responding to voice commands but was unable to  
speak because he remained on a ventilator, said critical care nurse 
Susie Faz. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawrence was near death when he was rushed to the hospital by  
paramedics, she said. 
</P>
<P>
	``When you come in with a temperature of 107, that's not very  
compatible with life,'' Faz said. ``He's a very lucky man.'' 
</P>
<P>
	His girlfriend opened their front door on Sunday after he had  
gone out for a jog and found him keeled over the doorstep, moaning 
and having trouble breathing, hospital spokeswoman Kris Carraway. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawrence arrived at the hospital and didn't regain consciousness  
until Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Suffering from heat exhaustion and acute hypothermia, he was  
treated with ice and fans by emergency doctors and nurses on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	A scan showed that his brain functions were unaffected, Ms.  
Carraway-Bowman said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unknown for which film he was preparing, but it was  
recently reported that he will star in ``See Spot Run,'' in which 
he'll play a postal worker who adopts a special dog. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
