<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Respect for Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The State Department is urging China not to  
prosecute leading members of the Falun Gong movement. 
</P>
<P>
	``The United States strongly believes that individual spiritual  
beliefs should be respected in accordance with international 
covenants that China has signed,'' spokesman James B. Foley said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Besides, Foley said, ``It's also our longstanding belief that no  
one should be persecuted for peaceful assembly, association or 
peaceful expression of their views.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Foley made the statement at a daily news briefing when asked  
about reports that the movement's leaders faced prosecution. 
</P>
<P>
	China banned the movement last month as a threat to political  
order. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
