<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Wednesday, Aug. 25, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Evening Stock Trading Set To Launch  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The race to bring after-hours stock trading to  
individual investors enters a new phase Wednesday in what amounts 
to the first real evening session on the East Coast and the first 
real afternoon session on the West Coast. The new session from 6 
p.m. to 8 p.m. Eastern time -- or 3 p.m. to 5 p.m. Pacific time -- is 
being offered Monday through Thursday for customers of Discover 
Brokerage and Dreyfus Brokerage Services on an electronic exchange 
named MarketXT. Only the discount broker Datek Online has 
officially launched an after-hours session -- from 4 p.m. to 5:15 
p.m. Eastern time. 

</P>
<P>
	Dow Closes at Record 11,326.04  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks thrived in the new interest rate  
environment today, shooting to record highs as investors expressed 
confidence that the U.S. economy can continue to grow without 
runaway inflation. At the close of trading on Wall Street, the Dow 
Jones industrial average was up 42.74 at 11,326.04, topping the 
previous record close of 11,299.76, set Monday. Broader stock 
indicators were also higher. The Nasdaq composite index, which 
lists most of the nation's leading technology companies, rose for a 
fourth straight session and is edging back toward its July 16 
record close of 2,864.48. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures as of Wednesday's close:  
Dow Industrials:        11326.04  + 42.74
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1612  Declines 1388  Unchgd  519
