<HEADLINE> Two Die in Train-Vehicle Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ELWOOD, Ill. (AP) -- An Amtrak train collided with a vehicle this  
morning, killing two people in the vehicle, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Will County authorities said no one aboard the train was hurt in  
the accident near Elwood, about 40 miles south of Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	An Amtrak spokesman in Chicago said he had no immediate details.  
  	   	
